A Registry is like "GitHub for Images." It is used to store your Docker images so you can use them anytime on any server.

Registry Commands
docker login: Opens the door to the registry using your Username and Password.

docker tag my-app user/my-app:v1: Puts a "Name Plate" (tag) on your image so the registry can identify it.

docker push user/my-app:v1: Uploads your image to the library (Registry).

docker pull user/my-app:v1: Downloads the image from the registry to a new server.
